  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_what-is-markdown-validator.dita" xtrc="shortdesc:1;25:14">markdown-validator is a rule-based tool that checks your Markdown files
  against editorial standards defined by your team. It catches missing metadata,
  incorrect front-matter values, and structural problems before your content reaches
  review or publication.</shortdesc>

  <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_what-is-markdown-validator.dita" xtrc="conbody:1;30:12">

    <note type="note" id="version-notice" class="- topic/note " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_what-is-markdown-validator.dita" xtrc="note:1;32:43">
      <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_what-is-markdown-validator.dita" xtrc="b:1;33:10">Applies to:</b> markdown-validator 0.2.x (last updated 2026-03-20).
      Planned changes in v0.3 (negation operator) and v0.4 (structured DOM)
      may affect rule behaviour described here.
    </note>

    <note type="important" id="blocked-pr" class="- topic/note " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_what-is-markdown-validator.dita" xtrc="note:2;38:44">
