    <section id="how-authors-use-it" class="- topic/section " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_what-is-markdown-validator.dita" xtrc="section:2;77:38">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_what-is-markdown-validator.dita" xtrc="title:3;78:14">How you use it</title>
      <ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_what-is-markdown-validator.dita" xtrc="ul:1;79:11">
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_what-is-markdown-validator.dita" xtrc="li:1;80:13"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_what-is-markdown-validator.dita" xtrc="b:5;80:16">Locally before a pull request</b> — run the tool from the command
        line to catch and fix problems before reviewers see them.</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_what-is-markdown-validator.dita" xtrc="li:2;82:13"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_what-is-markdown-validator.dita" xtrc="b:6;82:16">Automatically in CI/CD</b> — the pipeline validates every pull
        request. Required failures block the merge.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/concepts/c_what-is-markdown-validator.dita" xtrc="p:3;85:10">Your content lead maintains the rule set. You run the validator and fix
      what it reports.</p>
    </section>

